4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT EXPANDING THE BEST BEGINNINGS CHILD CARE
5 SCHOLARSHIP PROGRAM TO PROVIDE SCHOLARSHIPS TO CHILD-CARE WORKERS EMPLOYED BY A
6 LICENSED DAY-CARE CENTER OR REGISTERED FAMILY OR GROUP DAY-CARE HOME; PROVIDING
7 AN APPROPRIATION; AMENDING SECTIONS 52-2-714 AND 52-2-715, MCA; AND PROVIDING AN
8 EFFECTIVE DATE.”
9
10 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
11
12 Section 1. Section 52-2-714, MCA, is amended to read:
13 "52-2-714. Best beginnings child care scholarship program. There is a best beginnings child care
14 scholarship program administered by the department. The program is established to provide scholarships to
15 qualified low-income families and eligible child-care workers employed at a licensed day-care center or
16 registered family or group day-care home whose child received care provided by a licensed or registered child
17 care child-care provider or day-care facility."
18
19 Section 2. Section 52-2-715, MCA, is amended to read:
20 "52-2-715. Family income eligibility -- child-care worker eligibility -- requirements. (1) In Except
21 as provided in subsection (2), in determining income eligibility for qualified low-income families for the best
22 beginnings child care scholarship program, the department shall:
23 (1)(a) set a qualifying income threshold at no less than 185% of the federal poverty level for each
24 family size; and
25 (2)(b) set a maximum qualifying income level that is no higher than that allowed by the federal child
26 care and development block grant.
27 (2) (a) A child-care worker is eligible for the best beginnings child care scholarship program if the
28 worker is employed at a licensed day-care center or registered family or group day-care home and is engaged
